				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Is this being tested on a top-loader (HVC-* or NES-101) or a front-loader (NES-001)? It matters because a front-loader disables NMI on reset and a top-loader doesn't.<br /><br />My next direction is to log all writes to the mapper ($5000-$5FFF and $8000-$FFFF) from game start to reset, in order to test for defects in the implementation of the mapper in the CPLD that depend on write order. I remember <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=190120#p190120" class="postlink">FCEUX having such order dependencies</a>.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

